for font size

em is looking for parent element can be div if no div then body.it goes in compound problem ie parent multiple then fontsize goes out of control
rem looks for root element ie html and is more consistent for font size

for margin and padding and width etc

if we have font size and margin button in em then font size looks  for paent but marginbutton loooks for font size
but this is not in case of rem rem always looks for root element ie font size of html

Note use rem for font size for margin and padding use em (for button) ie padding automaticaly maintain according to font size

if used rem for margin and padding you will get consistent space 
 when we use rem for font size media querry ma html ko matra font size change gara pugcha




 //max width
 if use max width in px like 700px on changing view port above 700px content will lock
 all changes will exist below 700 px most time we use max width not min width


 //vh vmin vw vmax
 if height is in vh use vh for padding

